The social card of a resident of the Ivanovo region is recognized as an electronic means of payment.
The changes provide for the preservation of benefits for travel in public passenger transport.
From September 24, the procedure for organizing preferential travel for citizens using the social card of a resident of the Ivanovo region is changing.
According to the press service of the Russian government for the Ivanovo region, the changes provide for the preservation of benefits for travel in public passenger transport and bring the social card settlement scheme in line with the requirements of Federal Law No. 161 FZ &quot;On the National Payment System&quot;.
At the same time, the social card of a resident of the Ivanovo region is recognized as an electronic means of payment.
Accordingly, the conditions for its use are changing.
So, the replenishment limit is now set not on trips, as before, but in the amount of money, with the preservation of winter and summer periods - no more than 400 rubles in winter, in summer - no more than 800 rubles for the current month.
Now the holders of a social card on the receipts issued in transport will need to track not the number of remaining trips, but the balance of funds.
The cost of preferential travel for citizens will be 1/2 of the tariff in force with the carrier.
The remaining half of the fare is reimbursed by the regional budget.
The schedule for replenishing the social card with cash remains the same - from the 24th day of the previous month to the 23rd day of the current month.
The new procedure for traveling with a social card will have a number of advantages.
So, it becomes possible to keep a detailed account of spending money on a social card with an accuracy of kopecks.
In addition, it becomes possible to return credited, but unspent funds.
We also add that the scheme of mutual settlements with carriers is becoming transparent, since now a citizen pays half the fare, and the budget reimburses the carrier for exactly the same amount.
No commission will be charged when depositing funds to the card.
In turn, Vasily Silkin, Deputy Head of the Department of Roads and Transport of the Ivanovo Region, said that in 2014 more than 33 million trips were made in the region using a social card, in 2015 - almost 25 million trips.
More than 470 million rubles are allocated in the regional budget for the provision of preferential travel for citizens using a social card.
As of September 1, the amount of compensation for these purposes amounted to more than 312 million rubles.
