It seems unlikely that Cameron, being an admittedly active parent, is so unfamiliar with the contents of a book in which an unnamed boy learns about the destruction of the environment by the greedy tree cutter and necessities knitter Newhodkins, despite the protests of the Lorax (whose name is in the title of the book) - a funny creature with a mustache who &quot;speaks for the trees.&quot;
Most likely, such a simple PR task was entrusted to a performer who had never read a book about the Lorax to a child 20 times in a row.
