In turn, experts note that the main problem is the complete lack of infrastructure for the storage, maintenance and maintenance of yachts.
Owners prefer to store their vessels abroad - approximately €200 million annually go to the treasury of European states for the maintenance, repair and maintenance of yachts.
The Ministry of Economic Development of Russia has prepared a draft decision of the Council of the Eurasian Economic Commission &quot;On Amendments to the List of Goods Temporarily Imported with Full Conditional Relief from Customs Duties and Taxes&quot;, providing for full conditional exemption from customs duties and taxes in respect of imported yachts and other floating craft for recreation and sports.
