This year, the study of the Association of Russian Managers &quot;Top 1000 Russian Managers&quot; is published for the 16th time.
Being a tool for assessing the professional reputation of Russian top managers, the study sums up the work of Russian managers over the year, identifying leaders in industries and functional areas.
The initial pool of candidates consists of the winners of the previous year&#39;s ranking.
Last year&#39;s winners are invited to confirm their participation as a candidate for the current year&#39;s rankings and nominate members of their management team.
In addition, each of the candidates included in the initial list is invited to nominate up to ten new managers from other companies, which it would be advisable to add to the general pool of candidates.
It is possible to nominate the following heads of the company&#39;s functional areas: financial director, commercial director, marketing director, personnel director, IT director, public and corporate relations director, government relations director, corporate governance director.
Each manager proposed by the experts is invited to participate in the rating and is given the opportunity to nominate their management team and up to ten new leaders from other companies.
Candidates are nominated according to the sectoral principle based on the sectoral classifier of the Association of Managers: information technology, commercial banks, timber and wood processing industry, mechanical engineering, media business, metallurgy, diversified holdings, professional services, communications and telecommunications, service and production of consumer goods, insurance, construction, trade, transport, financial sector, pharmaceuticals, chemical industry, energy and fuel complex.
Each participant is given a login and password to enter the www.top1000.amr.ru website, where they can see information about other participants and can put down their assessments according to the criteria proposed for each functional area.
The rating methodology is based on the principle &quot;The best choose the best&quot;: top managers evaluate top managers, functional managers evaluate functional managers.
This principle allows you to get the most authentic assessment of the professional reputation of colleagues.
The final results of the rating are approved at meetings of expert commissions.
All interested candidates of the rating of the current year and multiple candidates of the rating of past years are invited to face-to-face meetings of expert commissions.
The commissions are organized on a functional basis: a commission for the approval of the list of top managers and eight commissions for the approval of the heads of functional areas.
At meetings of expert commissions, it is proposed to approve the submitted lists in alphabetical order (places are kept strictly according to the Internet assessment and are classified information until the rating is published) or to make adjustments to update them according to the attached list of reserve candidates.
The names of the companies are given in accordance with the rules of the Russian language and the norms of &quot;Kommersant&quot;.
At the time of publication of the rating, changes in the status of managers and companies are possible.
A comfortable rate for an investment loan is 10-13%.
According to experts, the market for lending to small and medium-sized businesses sank by 40% in January-April this year.
What do you think the situation is today?
After the panic at the end of 2014 - beginning of 2015, the volume of SME lending decreased significantly.
The reason is clear: a sharp increase in interest rates.
Lending at 25-30% per annum was not beneficial to anyone.
If earlier the bank could include all its possible problems in the future, from delays to defaults, into the increased rate, now it is impossible to do this: the rates are already exorbitant.
For businesses, the current level of interest rates on SME loans is uncomfortable.
For a significant part of investment projects, the current level is unacceptable in terms of their payback.
The rate level of 10-13% would allow businesses to invest in a wide range of projects and generate attractive returns on them.
To what extent, according to your estimates, is the demand of entrepreneurs for loans satisfied?
After the Central Bank lowered the interest rate, the situation improved slightly.
Credit resources have become more accessible.
However, according to our observations, customers began to apply for loans much less often.
First of all, business does not understand the prospects for its development and future income.
Today, business has one way out: it is necessary to learn how to work, focusing on the current economic situation in the country and region.
It is necessary to more closely monitor current results, control the movement of funds.
At the same time, if financial resources are available, it is worth using new technologies to modernize equipment, reduce production and energy supply costs.
All this, ultimately, allows the company to make products more competitive and keep the business even in an unstable economic situation.
What are the main trends in the SME lending market that will strengthen and influence its development until the end of 2015?
Will the interest rate change?
The forecast for lowering the average rate will largely depend on the policy of the Central Bank, and now the regulator is showing consistency in lowering the key rate.
However, a radical drop in the price of loans for SMEs should not be expected.
In the current situation, the problem, first of all, is inflation, which makes it necessary to increase the interest rate in order to generate real income.
In addition, the value of money in Russia will remain high even if the Central Bank cuts rates.
In terms of delinquency levels, traditionally small and medium-sized companies, limited both in their ability to replenish cash and in the options for correcting economic behavior, will certainly represent a greater risk for creditors.
I would not expect a significant reduction in the share of bad loans.
The main reason is international sanctions and their negative impact on the country&#39;s economy.
