A draft law on the indexation of social pensions, taking into account price increases, has been submitted to the Duma.
A draft law has been submitted to the State Duma providing for the indexation of social pensions annually from February 1, taking into account rising prices.
The author of the document, A Just Russia deputy Alexander Lomakin-Rumyantsev, also proposes to carry out additional indexation of pensions on April 1, if the growth rate of the subsistence minimum exceeds the growth rate of prices for goods and services.
The indexation of social pensions, in accordance with the current legislation, is carried out annually from April 1, taking into account the growth rate of the living wage for a pensioner in the Russian Federation over the past year.
The draft law, submitted to the lower chamber, provides for the introduction of indexation of social pensions, taking into account the growth rate of consumer prices.
At the same time, the first indexation is postponed to February 1, and the second is held on April 1.
