Where can I leave a review about the work of a bailiff in Murmansk?
The Office of the Federal Bailiff Service for the Murmansk Region reported that in order to improve the work to protect the rights and legitimate interests of citizens and organizations, the department has a book of reviews and suggestions.
In it, citizens can leave a record of the quality of work of bailiffs and other officials of the department, information about shortcomings in work, and also express their suggestions and wishes.
In management, a copy of the book of reviews and suggestions is located in the central hall, in a special pocket in a visible and accessible place at the checkpoint in the building.
In the structural divisions of management, the book is located in the office.
Taking into account the nature of the feedback or proposal, if necessary, a written response is sent to its initiator.
Xi Jinping calls for a more open economy to the world
The economy must become more open to the world to spur growth, President Xi Jinping said Tuesday in an address to a group tasked with leading reforms.
&quot;China should focus on attracting foreign investors and experts and develop a policy of opening up,&quot; he said addressing the 16th meeting of the Central Steering Group Committee on Comprehensively Deepening Reform.
Expanding opening up and deepening reforms will give new impetus and vitality to the economy and provide new space for economic development, he said.
The leading group adopted a number of directives, including introducing regulation of investor access to the market, changing border control rules, encouraging state-owned enterprises (SOEs) to attract private capital, and revising the system of registering residents.
According to the statement, a list of sectors of the economy and production that are not available for investment will be drawn up.
The system will be gradually debugged through trial programs.
This is an important step as it will give the market a greater role to play in allocating resources, enforcing the rule of law in business and increasing openness, the statement said.
The government will also loosen control over the powers it grants to companies, thus ensuring that companies run their own business.
The statement also said that China will allow border regions to explore new models of cross-border economic cooperation and new mechanisms to boost local growth.
Even more areas will be available to private investors in order to increase the openness of state-controlled sectors of the economy.
&quot;The government will not change its policy towards foreign investors and will protect the legitimate interests of foreign-funded companies, as well as provide them with better conditions,&quot; the statement said.
Additionally, the procedure for applying for a permanent residence permit for foreigners, or &quot;green card&quot;, will be facilitated by streamlining the requirements and simplifying the application process itself.
The meeting also discussed ensuring the rights of lawyers and issues of training professional judges and prosecutors.
Premier Li Keqiang and ministers Liu Yunshan and Zhang Gaoli also attended, according to an official report released after the meeting.
